 Summary


 &rdquo; } [/block] Authorized Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) occurs when a malicious resource forces a user&rsquo;s web browser to perform an unwanted action on a trusted website when the user is authenticated. The attack works because the browser requests automatically include all cookies, including session cookies.

