 Summary


 &rdquo; } [/block] A brute-force attack is an attempt of an attacker to discover a password by systematically trying every possible combination of letters, numbers, and symbols until revealing the correct combination. An attacker can always discover a password through the brute-force attack, but the downside is that it could take years to find it (depending on the password length and complexity, there could be trillions of possible combinations).

